pt.ul.fc.di.lasige.simhs.core.domain.scheduling.taxonomy

Interface IPartitionedScheduler

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IScheduler, java.util.Observer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MultiprocessorPartitionedScheduler, PartitionedRMScheduler

    public interface IPartitionedScheduler
extends IScheduler
    This interface belongs to a set of interfaces serving only the purpose of fitting schedulers into a priority- and migration-based taxonomy. Implementing this interface does not add to the methods that the class must implement, but rather allows using instanceof to verify properties of the scheduler (e.g., scheduler instanceof IFTPScheduler allows checking if a scheduler is a FTP (fixed task priority, RM-like) scheduler, if such knowledge is needed for schedulability analysis purposes.
